India’s Inflation to Soften From November, Ahluwalia Says

-- B y   S h a r a n g   L i m a y e
-- 
2011-10-18T08:00:13Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-18/india-s-inflation-to-soften-from-november-ahluwalia-says.html
India ’s inflation rate will start
softening from November and will be “signicantly lower” by
March next year,  Montek Singh Ahluwalia , deputy chairman of the
country’s Planning Commission, said in Hyderabad today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
